7139014|publisher=Connect6|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref> She then worked briefly at [[GlaxoSmithKline]] before returning to the University of Pennsylvania.<ref name=timeline />  Saouaf left the university and began a consulting business with pharmaceutical and biotechnical companies,<ref name=timeline /> hoping to help speed the process of discoveries for drugs to treat autoimmune disease. In 2012, together with University of Pennsylvania colleagues, she \"discovered a possible treatment approach...through oral drugs\" and founded Atlantic Bio Sci, LLC.<ref name=bio /> In 2013, she won a Fellowship from the Alliance of Women Entrepreneurs.<ref name=trials>{{cite web|title=Meet Our 2013 Fellows|url=http://www.phillyawe.org/2013-fellows|publisher=Alliance of Women Entrepreneurs|accessdate=25 November 2015|location=Pottstown, Pennsylvania|date=2013}}</ref>\n\n==Selected works==\n*{{cite journal |last1=Weiner |first1=D B|last2=Williams|first2=W V|last3=Siegel|first3=R M|last4=Jerrold-Jones|first4=S |display-authors=etal |date=January 1989|title=Molecular characterization of suppressor T cells|url= |journal=Transplantation Proceedings|volume=20|issue=6 |pages=1151\u20131153|doi= |pmid=2974197}}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Siegel|first1=Richard M|last2=Katsumata|first2=Makoto|last3=Komori|first3=Shinji|last4=Jerrold-Jones|first4=Sandra |display-authors=etal |date=December 1990|title=Mechanisms of Autoimmunity in the Context of T-Cell Tolerance: Insights from Natural and Transgenic Animal Model Systems|journal=Immunological Reviews|volume=118|issue=1|pages=165\u2013192|doi=10.1111/j.1600-065X.1990.tb00816.x|pmid=2150401}}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Saouaf|first1=Sandra J|last2=Mahajan|first2=Sandeep|last3=Rowley|first3=R Bruce|last4=Kut|first4=Stephanie A |display-authors=etal |date=September 1994|title=Temporal Differences in the Activation of Three Classes of Non-Transmembrane Protein Tyrosine Kinases Following B-Cell Antigen Receptor Surface Engagement|url= |journal=Proc